Race.SpecificTitle: PW Millage Prop. No. 1 -- 3 Mills - PJ - 3 Yrs.
Race.FullText: Shall the Parish of East Carroll, State of Louisiana (the "Parish"), levy a special tax of three (3) mills on all the property subject to taxation in the Parish (an estimated $124,500 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the tax for an entire year), for a period of three (3) years, beginning with the year 2016 and ending with the year 2018, for the purpose of supporting the Parish's General Fund?

Race.SpecificTitle: PW Millage Renewal Prop. No. 2 -- 1 Mill - PJ - 3 Yrs.
Race.FullText: Shall the Parish of East Carroll, State of Louisiana (the "Parish"), levy a special tax of one (1) mill on all the property subject to taxation in the Parish (an estimated $41,500 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the tax for an entire year), for a period of three (3) years, beginning with the year 2016 and ending with the year 2018, for the purpose of operating and maintaining the Byerley House (Tourism Center)?

Race.SpecificTitle: PW Millage Renewal Prop. No. 3 -- 2 Mills - PJ - 3 Yrs.
Race.FullText: Shall the Parish of East Carroll, State of Louisiana (the "Parish"), levy a special tax of two (2) mills on the property subject to taxation in the Parish (an estimated $83,000 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the tax for an entire year), for a period of three (3) years, beginning with the year 2016 and ending with the year 2018, for the purpose of operating and maintaining the Louisiana State Cotton Museum?

Race.SpecificTitle: Garbage District No. 1 -- 11.67 Mills - PJ - 5 Yrs.
Race.FullText: Shall Garbage District No. 1 of the Parish of East Carroll, State of Louisiana (the "District"), levy an eleven and sixty-seven hundredths (11.67) mills tax on all the property subject to taxation in the District (an estimated $386,800 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the tax for an entire year), for a period of five (5) years, beginning with the year 2016 and ending with the year 2020, for the purpose of providing and maintaining garbage collection and disposal services for the District, including necessary equipment and facilities therefor, said millage to represent a one-hundredths of a mill (.01) increase over the 11.66 mills tax authorized to be levied through the year 2015 pursuant to an election held on October 22, 2011?
